Terraform AWS Infrastructure Project
   Project Overview
This project creates a complete AWS infrastructure using Terraform with best practices:
    • VPC with public and private subnets across multiple AZs 
    • 2 EC2 instances running Apache web servers 
    • Application Load Balancer distributing traffic across instances 
    • Security groups with proper isolation 
    • Modular structure for maintainability

Project Structure
terraform-aws-project/
├── versions.tf          # Terraform and provider versions
├── variables.tf         # Input variables
├── terraform.tfvars     # Variable values
├── vpc.tf              # VPC configuration
├── security.tf         # Security groups
├── compute.tf          # EC2 instances
├── alb.tf              # Application Load Balancer
├── outputs.tf          # Output values
├── user_data.sh        # EC2 bootstrap script
├── screenshots/         # Screenshot
│   ├── plan.png
│   ├── apply.png
│   ├── Instance1.png
│   └── Instance2.png
└── README.md           # This file

